reversible physicist writes "The Electronic Frontier Foundation has
[0]sued spoon-bender Uri Geller for using 'baseless copyright claims' to
silence critics who question his paranormal powers. Brian Sapient posted
on YouTube a 14-minute excerpt from the 1993 PBS NOVA program 'Secrets of
the Psychics,' in which skeptic James Randi says Geller's spoon-bending
feats were simple tricks. YouTube took down the video after Geller
complained — his lawyers claim that 10 seconds of the video are owned by
Geller. A [1]shorter excerpt of the video is still up on YouTube."

