| iPod/iPhone Nano With Touch Panel?                                 |
|   from the they-feel-you dept.                                     |
|   posted by Zonk on Friday May 11, @17:21 (Media (Apple))          |
|   http://apple.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/11/2028232        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Staska writes "A new [1]Apple patent filing shows new directions for
Apple's touch interface design. For smaller devices like iPod Nano,
touchscreen interface may not be feasible — the screen is just too small
for touch operation. According to the patent, Apple can still make full
screen iPods and put a touch panel on the backside of the device with
transparent controls on the front screen. In addition to iPod, patent
filing also describes controls for the phone. ZDNet even thinks that
[2]this patent can hint about future touch interfaces for all Apple
products."

